{"word":"συ","slug":"συ","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>συ</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:Substantive'>subst.</a> <a href='S:Pronoun'>Pron.</a> of the second <a href='S:person, personal'>pers.</a>, <i>thou, you.</i><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:strengthened'>strengthd.</a> by <a href='S:composition'>compos.</a> with the enclit. <el>γε</el>, <el>σύγε</el>, (like <el>ἔγωγε</el>) <i>thou at least, for thy part</i>, in <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>, doric <el>τύγα</el> <b><a href='S:Theocritus'>Theocr.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>Dual <a href='S:nominative'>nom.</a> and <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <el>σφῶι</el>, <i>you two, both of you</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>III. </b><a href='S:plural'>Pl.</a> <i>ye, you</i>, <b><a href='S:Homer'>Hom.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>,<p/></div>"}]}